I had a small oil leak in my '92 Grand Prix. It had the 3.1L V6 motor. The
leak turned out to be an oil pump drive seal or something like that. The
little rubber seal only cost 50 or so cents. As for the steering wheel
moving up and down I had that problem too. If you're problem is exactly the
same as mine, it could be very difficult and dangerous to drive the car. I
only drove mine for a couple of days before junking the entire car (there
were other problems as well and well over 300,000).
Grand Prix's are good cars and will last a long time if they are and have
been maintained but I would definitely get that tilt steering wheel problem
looked at if I were you.

