The broken steering is a safety hazard; if your state or whatever has
any sort of safety inspection, they may not catch it; but YOU should.
Do NOT drive this car with a broken lock.

Evidence of oil leaking: is there any used oil build-up underneath?
Note that the design of this car makes engine work more expensive; if
you have any reason to remove the heads, it will cost $1500 or more,
probably as much as the car is worth.

Also, watch out for the windows. Replacing power window servos runs
$500 - each. And does it have a computer chip? THAT can run $800 or
more to replace; and it is NOT negotiable: if the chip dies, the car
stops running.

Fun car over all. Maybe worth $500? If you enjoy it, do the repairs and
have fun, but keep in mind that a car that old - especially a Grand Prix
- may not have much time left before the junkyard.

